# Branching Model (authoritative)

The remote has two long-lived branches:

| Branch | Role | Deploys to |
|--------|------|------------|
| `main` | Production source of truth | equipqr.app (Vercel Production) |
| `preview` | **Legacy — being retired (#1033).** Do not branch off or target in new work. | — |

There is **no `dev` branch**. Solo-developer workflow: **one feature branch at a time → PR → `main`.**

## Rules for agents

1. **Branch off `main`** for new feature, fix, refactor, chore, or experimental work — unless the user explicitly says **hotfix** (still branches off `main` for the fix PR).
2. **All PRs target `main` by default.** Do not open PRs into `preview`.
3. When the GitHub default branch and this rule disagree on integration flow, **this rule wins** for day-to-day work. Production releases still promote `main` on Vercel manually when ready.
4. Before creating a branch:
   ```powershell
   git fetch origin main
   git switch -c feat/<short-name> origin/main
   ```
5. When opening a PR:
   ```powershell
   gh pr create --base main --head feat/<short-name> --title "<conventional-commit title>"
   ```
6. **Preview / QA URLs:**
   - Each PR gets a Vercel **Preview** deployment URL automatically.
   - Stable hostname **`preview.equipqr.app`** tracks the latest successful **Preview** deployment (not the retired Vercel custom `staging` environment or git `preview` branch).
   - Supabase **ephemeral PR branches** validate `supabase/**` changes while the PR is open.
   - Integration OAuth (Google Workspace, QuickBooks): verify on the **local stack** before merge (`local-verify-before-preview-push.mdc`).
7. **Hotfix:** Branch off `origin/main`, PR into `main`, deploy via production promotion.
8. **Local E2E before merge.** No merge to `main` until `local-verify-before-preview-push.mdc` passes with zero user manual steps.
9. **Worktree gates the workflow tempo:**
   - **Main worktree (`C:\Users\viral\EquipQR`) on `main`:** direct push after local verification when the user authorizes push-to-main (protected branch — typically merge via PR).
   - **Linked worktrees (`~/.cursor/worktrees/EquipQR/`):** formal PR merge-ready workflow per `pr-merge-ready-workflow.mdc`.
   - **`main` stays protected.** Never force-push to `main`.

See git-powershell.mdc for Windows worktree cleanup gotchas.

## Why this changed (#1033)

Persistent git `preview` + Supabase branch `olsdirk` duplicated PR preview + ephemeral branching. Solo velocity is **feature → main** with Vercel Preview + Supabase PR branches for schema validation.
